headline: Australia Strikes Deal to Resettle Refugees in U.S.
summary: Some of the hundreds of refugees being held in Australia-backed Pacific island camps are to be resettled in the U.S. under a one-time deal between the countries.

summary: Colombia‘s government announced a new peace pact with the Marxist FARC rebel group on Saturday, capping six feverish weeks of negotiations.

headline: Paris’s Bataclan Reopens a Year After Massacre
summary: A concert by British artist Sting at the Bataclan night at once honored those who died in the attack a year ago and celebrated the theater’s revival.

headline: Blast at Pakistan Shrine Kills More Than 50 People
summary: Islamic State claimed the deadly bomb attack at a Muslim shrine in southern Pakistan, which officials said killed at least 52 people and wounded 106.

headline: GM Bets on Chevy Bolt to Jump-Start Market
summary: The Chevrolet Bolt, after two decades of false starts on electric vehicles, represents one of General Motors Chief Executive Mary Barra’s biggest bets on the auto giant’s ability to jump-start an underdeveloped market.

headline: Philippines Returns $15 Million Stolen From Bangladesh Account at N.Y. Fed
summary: Philippine authorities returned $15 million of $81 million stolen from Bangladesh’s account at the Federal Reserve Bank of New York in a February cyberheist, the first time the South Asian country has been able to retrieve any of the stolen money.

headline: Reeling Democrats Now Face Identity Crisis
summary: Democrats, reeling from their election defeats, are facing an identity crisis and leadership vacuum that is shaping debate over who will be the next chairman of the Democratic National Committee.

headline: Fargo to Keep Saving Its Pennies in Hopes of Defeating Floods
summary: Residents in Fargo, N.D., and a nearby county will be pooling their pennies for another 68 years to help cover a massive, multibillion-dollar channel around the city to divert floodwaters from the Red River.

headline: Retirement Policy Under Trump? Unclear, but There Are Clues
summary: Donald Trump hasn’t said a lot about Social Security funding or other retirement-savings policies, but his few comments—along with congressional Republicans’ proposals—provide some insight on what to expect.

headline: How to Win at Brunch: It’s All in the Timing
summary: Savvy cooks take the stress out of entertaining by plotting a master meal game plan. Use these recipes and this timeline to pull off an elegant brunch for eight with your equanimity intact.

headline: SAIC Motor Set to Build and Sell Audis in China
